(window.webpackJsonp=window.webpackJsonp||[]).push([[21],{113:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"metadata":{"timed":true,"story ID":"a97277ba-1d54-420c-84d8-1ed0718f6f80","title":{"_default":"AAHP_629_John_Booth_1-13-2009"},"media":{"audio":"","video":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=anBjLKTT07M"},"languages":[],"date_created":"","date_uploaded":"10/15/2025","source":{"_default":""},"description":"","genre":"","author":"","glosser":"","speakers":[],"xml_file_name":"AAHP_629_John_Booth_1-13-2009.eaf","source_filetype":"ELAN","tier IDs":{"Speaker 0":{"subdivided":false},"Speaker 1":{"subdivided":false},"Speaker 2":{"subdivided":false}},"speaker IDs":{"S1":{"tier":"Speaker 0"},"S2":{"tier":"Speaker 1"},"S3":{"tier":"Speaker 2"}}},"sentences":[{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":0,"end_time_ms":28000,"num_slots":1,"text":"All right, this is Marna Westin on Tuesday, January 13th, 2009, interviewing for the oral, the Sam Proctor Oral History, uh, project at the University of Florida. I\'m at the, uh, Gator Dining Facility and this interview is with Mr. John Booth, who has been, uh, lead Cook here with the University of Florida for some time and also been on the campus for some time. And we\'re just gonna begin to talk to him. I wanna thank you Mr. Booth, for allowing us to do the interview.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":28000,"end_time_ms":29000,"num_slots":1,"text":"No problem.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":29000,"end_time_ms":33000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Uh, would you please spell, uh, your complete name, please?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":33000,"end_time_ms":39000,"num_slots":1,"text":"My name is John Booth, J-O-H-N-H, period, which is Henry B-O-O-T-H.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":39000,"end_time_ms":40000,"num_slots":1,"text":"And what\'s your date of birth, please?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":40000,"end_time_ms":42000,"num_slots":1,"text":"3/28/46.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":42000,"end_time_ms":45000,"num_slots":1,"text":"3/28/46. Okay. My birthday is three twenty one, so yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":45000,"end_time_ms":46000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. Mm-hmm <affirmative>.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":46000,"end_time_ms":50000,"num_slots":1,"text":"And how long have you been employed with the University of Florida?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":50000,"end_time_ms":51000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Since 1978.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":51000,"end_time_ms":53000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. And what was your first job here? First","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":53000,"end_time_ms":76000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Job was taking care of athletes in yarn hall. I worked for two previous food service company from 78 to 82. Then I went to work for the University Athletic Association from 82 up until 96. And at that time when Aramark Corporation came in and the private dining room was phased out, we\'ve been in this building since 1996. Mm-hmm","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":76000,"end_time_ms":85000,"num_slots":1,"text":"<affirmative>. I actually have eaten in this building before my Kiwanis Club used to do the seven o\'clock, um, breakfast. Right. And so we ate those outta this room, or we were on the other side, but we were here at seven o\'clock.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":85000,"end_time_ms":115000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Right. Okay. Well, we got a nice <inaudible> facility here. We built in 1996 and with the direction of the Aramark Corporation, which, uh, in charge of all food service on campus, we got 40 or better food service campus on this campus. And everyone is related to the <inaudible> Corporation, which they branch out to the students needs because their time going, the student needs changes. So they\'re the ones most updated companies that I\'ve been working for since I\'ve been here. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So it\'s not a bad, not a bad place to work. Mm-hmm","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":115000,"end_time_ms":116000,"num_slots":1,"text":"<affirmative>. And","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":116000,"end_time_ms":126000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Go ahead. Amark Corporation, you get to see a lot of people come and go. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And a lot of students. Every four years we have a new batch of students that comes in, but we enjoy all of \'em, so No problem.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":126000,"end_time_ms":129000,"num_slots":1,"text":"So you work with all the students to help you with those needs, but you mentioned something","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":129000,"end_time_ms":131000,"num_slots":1,"text":"About Mainly I, mainly in the food service.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":131000,"end_time_ms":132000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":132000,"end_time_ms":145000,"num_slots":1,"text":"So I just do the food service and athletes during the athlete season. During the fall season, we run summer camps, so we involved with students and athletes at some point in time, but mainly, mostly athletes.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":145000,"end_time_ms":147000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. Um, where were you born, Mr. Booth? I","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":147000,"end_time_ms":150000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Was born in Gainesville, Florida, 1946.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":150000,"end_time_ms":152000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. And would you tell us about your parents, please? My","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":152000,"end_time_ms":170000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Parents were born in South Florida and moved in their early, in their early ages. They were raised around the Lake Cross area, which is near Alway. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And my mothers deceased dad deceased, but I have eight brothers and four sisters. Okay. So we was raised, they all in this area generally.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":170000,"end_time_ms":172000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Could you, uh, tell me your brothers and sisters names, please? Yeah,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":172000,"end_time_ms":193000,"num_slots":1,"text":"We had one brothers named James Walter, Joseph, Isaiah, Willie Davis, Jeremiah and James Arthur, and I have four sisters, Inez, Martha, Pearl, and Felicia.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":193000,"end_time_ms":195000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. And what was your dad\'s full name?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":195000,"end_time_ms":197000,"num_slots":1,"text":"John Henry Booth Jr.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":197000,"end_time_ms":198000,"num_slots":1,"text":"And your","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":198000,"end_time_ms":201000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Mother? Uh, Sadie Booth Dickinson.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":201000,"end_time_ms":204000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. Um, so her, her, what was her","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":204000,"end_time_ms":205000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Maiden name? Maid name? Sadie Dickinson.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":205000,"end_time_ms":208000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Sadie Dickinson. And were they also from Gainesville?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":208000,"end_time_ms":210000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah. And whole life here? Whole life","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":210000,"end_time_ms":211000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Here? Mm-hmm","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":211000,"end_time_ms":214000,"num_slots":1,"text":"<affirmative>. Do you remember, um, your grandparents?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":214000,"end_time_ms":220000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Grandparents were raised in South Florida, but they was passed at the time? I was becoming of age, so I don\'t really remember. Do","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":220000,"end_time_ms":221000,"num_slots":1,"text":"You recall their names?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":221000,"end_time_ms":228000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah, Daisy. Daisy. My grandmother\'s name was Daisy Pearl Dickinson, the grandfather I\'m not familiar with.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":228000,"end_time_ms":232000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. Is that your, um, your mother, your mom\'s side or your dad\'s side?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":232000,"end_time_ms":233000,"num_slots":1,"text":"On the mom\'s side. On the mom\'s side.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":233000,"end_time_ms":243000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Other side? I don\'t remember those. My daddy passed at an early age also when I was around 12 years old. So his parents were from Birmingham, Alabama in that area. So I\'m not familiar with those. Mm-hmm","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":243000,"end_time_ms":245000,"num_slots":1,"text":"<affirmative>. So you\'ve lived primarily in the south, south?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":245000,"end_time_ms":247000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Okay.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":247000,"end_time_ms":251000,"num_slots":1,"text":"What is your earliest memory of school? Where\'d you go to elementary school? I went","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":251000,"end_time_ms":262000,"num_slots":1,"text":"To school at do all elementary, Williams Elementary school. Finished school at Lincoln High School in 1963. Okay.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":262000,"end_time_ms":271000,"num_slots":1,"text":"I just met the, uh, assistant principal at Lincoln the other day. Mr. Lawson Brown, junior. Right. Right. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Very proud of the history at Lincoln. Lincoln","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":271000,"end_time_ms":276000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah. That must be, um, a great source of, uh, fond memories for you now,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":276000,"end_time_ms":294000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Right. Because it\'s, at the time we were going, it was not integrated. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. The segregated school. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So it was, it had two high schools, primarily Gainesville High and Lincoln High for the black kids. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And the Gainesville High was for the white kids. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Whatever. But now things, things have changed. I\'ve seen a lot of things changes. It\'s better for the better.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":294000,"end_time_ms":297000,"num_slots":1,"text":"The Lincoln High was where a Quin Jones is now, correct?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":297000,"end_time_ms":309000,"num_slots":1,"text":"The original Lincoln High. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. But the new Lincoln High is over on where the Lincoln Middle School is now. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. But, but the majority of people, the game they went to, the old Lincoln High School is where the old a Quin Jones building is now. Mm-hmm <affirmative>.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":309000,"end_time_ms":310000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":310000,"end_time_ms":337000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Do you think that, um, it was, it was better going to school that way? And I ask, um, uh, not just for total judgment, but you know, now a lot of teachers don\'t even know the kids. Right. They don\'t know the name. There\'s all discipline problems. But I\'ve talked to my dad and he talked about how well everybody graduated, everybody was prepared with a trade. The teachers, they knew your name, you know? Right. Anybody could, you know. Correct. And offer some discipline and some love, uh, you know, to the, to the kids in the school, but it\'s not the same now. Do you see kind of that same thing, or","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":337000,"end_time_ms":350000,"num_slots":1,"text":"It\'s better in a way, but it\'s better for the kids because they can kind of interact with other kids and learn from it. At that time. We come over, we didn\'t have the opportunity that the kids have now mm-hmm <affirmative>. So I think it\'s much better now than it\'s worth it.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":350000,"end_time_ms":353000,"num_slots":1,"text":"When you say you didn\'t have the opportunity, what do you mean by that?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":353000,"end_time_ms":380000,"num_slots":1,"text":"But the sources wasn\'t there for the kids then, like it is now. So things are made more available for kids nowadays in were then you mean the books? Parents make more money books and parents make a little bit more money than they did then, and the books are more freely distributed to among the kids than they were then. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. At the time when we went to school, we got the use books that the other schools hand down. Now things are different. So he pretty much, he\'s pretty much better than they were before.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":380000,"end_time_ms":382000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Did you have a favorite teacher in school?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":382000,"end_time_ms":391000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh yeah. Lot of, uh, miss Neely. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Mr. Jackson. Yeah. It, it was nice teachers. They quite took up time with you, which was nice.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":391000,"end_time_ms":406000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah. I was, um, meeting with, um, um, someone from Lincoln a couple weeks ago, and they told me that one of their teachers has breakfast at Shoney\'s every Sunday morning. Okay. Um, it might be Mr. Jackson if he\'s still living. Yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":406000,"end_time_ms":408000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Leonard Jackson. Okay.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":408000,"end_time_ms":412000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Yeah. And, uh, what kind of a teacher, what subject did he teach?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":412000,"end_time_ms":416000,"num_slots":1,"text":"He was like in the English teacher area in that area and","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":416000,"end_time_ms":434000,"num_slots":1,"text":"But see, some of the teachers had a dual role mm-hmm <affirmative>. In those days, so they taught two different subjects mm-hmm <affirmative>. So, but, but it was, it was good. You learned a lot mm-hmm <affirmative>. Because like I said, then the teachers had more time with you because the class was smaller mm-hmm <affirmative>. But with the minor of kids they got going to school today, it\'s kind of, you know, it\'s kind of hard.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":434000,"end_time_ms":436000,"num_slots":1,"text":"What was your favorite subject?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":436000,"end_time_ms":438000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Uh, math. English. Wow.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":438000,"end_time_ms":448000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah, because I like numbers. Uhhuh, I like figuring out numbers. I like counting writing. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. It was, it was nice. It was a good, it was a good learning.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":448000,"end_time_ms":451000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Is that something that served you throughout your, your career","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":451000,"end_time_ms":462000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Work? Oh, yeah. It helped that a lot because of the kind of work I\'m doing now. You got to have numbers, you gotta be able to read the menus and the recipes that you be given, so it helps out a lot. Oh yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":462000,"end_time_ms":466000,"num_slots":1,"text":"So did you go to Lincoln from one to to 12?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":466000,"end_time_ms":470000,"num_slots":1,"text":"No, at the time we went to from seven to 12.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":470000,"end_time_ms":471000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. From seven to 12.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":471000,"end_time_ms":484000,"num_slots":1,"text":"You do all elementary? Mm-hmm <affirmative>. From one to six. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And then Lincoln was seven to 12, but now we didn\'t have the middle schools. He was school one through six, six through 12.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":484000,"end_time_ms":486000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Elementary school, secondary school, seventh","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":486000,"end_time_ms":489000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Or fifth. So it wasn\'t, wasn\'t no such thing as a middle school at that time. Mm-hmm","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":489000,"end_time_ms":493000,"num_slots":1,"text":"<affirmative>. What kind of activities and clubs were you involved in in school? What\'d you like to do?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":493000,"end_time_ms":495000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Mostly basketball.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":495000,"end_time_ms":496000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":496000,"end_time_ms":498000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Mainly basketball. That was my main subject. I loved","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":498000,"end_time_ms":500000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Basketball. What position did you play?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":500000,"end_time_ms":501000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Point guard.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":501000,"end_time_ms":502000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh, you point guard. So I","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":502000,"end_time_ms":505000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Wasn\'t good, but I was there <laugh>. Okay. I was on the team. I showed up. I was there.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":505000,"end_time_ms":507000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. Did you like to shoot or did you like to pass? I","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":507000,"end_time_ms":515000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Liked shoot <laugh>. Yeah. That was <laugh>. Yeah. That was, that was the best, best. It was a good times.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":515000,"end_time_ms":516000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Did you all have a strong team? Yeah,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":516000,"end_time_ms":518000,"num_slots":1,"text":"We had a good team. I, who,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":518000,"end_time_ms":519000,"num_slots":1,"text":"I didn\'t Who, who\'s the coach?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":519000,"end_time_ms":524000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Well, it been so long, I don\'t remember. Oh, Mr. T first.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":524000,"end_time_ms":528000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Wow. TB Macon. Yeah. Yeah. Wow. That\'s, that\'s the real name of the community right there.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":528000,"end_time_ms":541000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah. Because they got a recreation center that named Neer him. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Over in Southeast Gainesville. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And he was a great teacher. And he had, he know he be strict, but he made sure he got the, got the work done. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. It worked out. Worked.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":541000,"end_time_ms":545000,"num_slots":1,"text":"What was his theory of being a coach? Like how, what, what, what do you remember about him that made him a good","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":545000,"end_time_ms":559000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Coach, but he wanted to make sure that you were clean. He was on time and you participated in all the activity that was there for you. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. He was a strong leader. He wanted to make sure that you did what you\'re supposed to do. So it worked out. It worked out great.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":559000,"end_time_ms":560000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Did y\'all have study hall?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":560000,"end_time_ms":573000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh yes. Study hall was first period, sometimes. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Yes. Oh yeah. We had mainly all the subject, all the things they have now. Were just on different scales. Most scale back version of it. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. But we had pretty much all the time thing they had. Now,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":573000,"end_time_ms":576000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Who was your strongest rival in sports?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":576000,"end_time_ms":589000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Uh, wasn\'t no East Side, so it had to be GH, uh, let\'s see, Lincoln, well, most of the schools in the area. Let\'s see. Hm. I\'m not familiar, but I\'m not","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":589000,"end_time_ms":591000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Sure. Did y\'all play Vanguard?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":591000,"end_time_ms":592000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Vanguard?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":592000,"end_time_ms":593000,"num_slots":1,"text":"There\'s Ocala School,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":593000,"end_time_ms":610000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Ocala Schools Possibility? I\'m not quite certain about that. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. But I know we played a lot of the, well see that time the black schools were playing the black schools. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So you could pretty much figure out who we was playing. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. But there wasn\'t no Gainesville High against Lincoln Height at that time","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":610000,"end_time_ms":611000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Because","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":611000,"end_time_ms":612000,"num_slots":1,"text":"It was segregated. Segregated. Mm-hmm","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":612000,"end_time_ms":615000,"num_slots":1,"text":"<affirmative>. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Yeah. Would y\'all have beaten him if you played him?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":615000,"end_time_ms":622000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Most likely. Probably would\'ve. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Yeah. We would\'ve tried our best anyway. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Yeah. Okay. Alright.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":622000,"end_time_ms":631000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Well back to the University of Florida. What would you say has been the biggest change that\'s occurred since you\'ve been here?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":631000,"end_time_ms":661000,"num_slots":1,"text":"I\'ve seen more black kids on campus than I see when I first came here, which is a great, great thing for the school. And I\'ve seen a lot of changes when I came here. The old dawn wasn\'t there. We had bleaches in the South end zone, and I seen it\'s, it\'s the whole, the whole atmosphere on campus has changed. It\'s, it\'s, it\'s a more better place. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And it\'s more friendly place and it\'s more open to all students now. So it is not bad. It\'s not bad.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":661000,"end_time_ms":667000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Was, uh, Gainesville really big on the segregation, you know, downtown? You couldn\'t go to the theaters and do stuff like that, or,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":667000,"end_time_ms":688000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh, pretty much like any other town. Yeah. In the early days mm-hmm <affirmative>. But they, every, we had a theater downtown. They had a theater on Fifth Avenue. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So we always had some place to go, you know, so it wasn\'t like we didn\'t have any place to go at all mm-hmm <affirmative>. But we had a place to go. So it was to for yourself. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Then they, so we, we wasn\'t so bad. We survived","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":688000,"end_time_ms":696000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Once there were more, you know, black students on campus, in the community. Did they do most of their socializing in the Fifth Avenue area as well?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":696000,"end_time_ms":711000,"num_slots":1,"text":"No, they started them, uh, mainly with all the other kids. Okay. So it wasn\'t just one area. When it started getting more integrated, they all started blending together. They all going to clubs together. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. It wasn\'t just like it was in the old days. No.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":711000,"end_time_ms":715000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Did you have a lot of communication with, um, like the first black students that came to campus? Did they","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":715000,"end_time_ms":719000,"num_slots":1,"text":"No, I was mainly concentrate on food service. I didn\'t get into no politics or nothing like","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":719000,"end_time_ms":722000,"num_slots":1,"text":"That. I mean, just talking to \'em, you know, like, Hey, how you doing?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":722000,"end_time_ms":750000,"num_slots":1,"text":"That was because I was, no, I was speaking to athletes. I was only involved and that if I see a student on the street, I was speak to \'em mm-hmm <affirmative>. No matter what, you know, who they were, whatever. But I didn\'t get involved \'cause I was mainly inside concentrating on food service. Okay. Because you\'re not, when you\'re in yard hall, you\'re in the back of the stadium. The food was like an isolated area. So you\'re behind the stadium. Behind the hall was behind the stadium. So you didn\'t get a chance to see the people out in the street every, all the time. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. But it was Okay.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":750000,"end_time_ms":753000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Did you, um, know the first black athletes that were here?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":753000,"end_time_ms":755000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh yeah, I know some of \'em. Yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":755000,"end_time_ms":758000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Uh, Mr. Jackson,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":758000,"end_time_ms":760000,"num_slots":1,"text":"I met Tyrone, uh, oh, early days.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":760000,"end_time_ms":762000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Mm-hmm <affirmative>.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":762000,"end_time_ms":767000,"num_slots":1,"text":"He had a guy from Jacksonville,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S3","tier":"Speaker 2","start_time_ms":767000,"end_time_ms":770000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Let\'s see a minute.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":770000,"end_time_ms":781000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Gaffney. Wendy Gaffney. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Yeah. Gaffney. Then Tyrone Young came, came along. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And then we started after, started getting more and more as the years went by. Mm-hmm","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S3","tier":"Speaker 2","start_time_ms":781000,"end_time_ms":785000,"num_slots":1,"text":"<affirmative>. So","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":785000,"end_time_ms":791000,"num_slots":1,"text":"What were the crowds like, um, you know, for the, like a football game weekend? Was that something that you had experience with?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":791000,"end_time_ms":807000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh yeah. We had to work every football weekend. Mm-hmm. Anyway. \'cause we was doing food service for the athletes. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And the parents, some on campus. So we said we was already involved because we always worked football service anyway. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. That was just part of the, part of the work.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":807000,"end_time_ms":813000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Well, walk us through a football Saturday. What, what, what would you get up? What would you do? How long would you be on campus? What kind of things","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":813000,"end_time_ms":843000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Happened? Campus was like six until beginning of the game. Six in the morning until, whatever, if it\'s the early game, you come in there early. If it\'s a late game, you come a little later, but you, you in there two or three hours prior to the game. An hour before, after the game starts. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So your typical day is six to seven hours on game day, which is, you know, which is involved getting food prepared for the people that, you know, coming in the dining room. So you\'re there, have everything ready when the doors open?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":843000,"end_time_ms":846000,"num_slots":1,"text":"The, the players, the parents, the coaches? No,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":846000,"end_time_ms":849000,"num_slots":1,"text":"The players and parents. On game day, we don\'t, we don\'t see them.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":849000,"end_time_ms":856000,"num_slots":1,"text":"They live in the motel the night before, so we don\'t see them at a 30, we don\'t see \'em anymore. Okay. Till Monday. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Or Sunday.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":856000,"end_time_ms":858000,"num_slots":1,"text":"But the players would come in?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":858000,"end_time_ms":861000,"num_slots":1,"text":"No, the players, no, they in motel.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":861000,"end_time_ms":864000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. Well then who were you preparing food for?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":864000,"end_time_ms":865000,"num_slots":1,"text":"For the public.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":865000,"end_time_ms":874000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh, okay. For like people to buy at the stadium and stuff like that. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Okay. Yeah. So you would cook for, I guess it was I guess 45,000, 50,000 people? No. First started? No,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":874000,"end_time_ms":877000,"num_slots":1,"text":"No, no, no. We only cook for the press people.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":877000,"end_time_ms":879000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Ah, the special public. Yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":879000,"end_time_ms":891000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. Not especially the press mm-hmm <affirmative>. For the press mm-hmm <affirmative>. And the public eats wherever they want to eat at. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. We didn\'t take care of that. We just was preparing food for the press box,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":891000,"end_time_ms":893000,"num_slots":1,"text":"The, the president\'s box and that kind of stuff. No","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":893000,"end_time_ms":909000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Fresh box. We had nothing to do with the president box. Okay. This is, that\'s a separate part. Okay. It\'s a, the people that write the newspapers and stuff that we just do that mm-hmm <affirmative>. But we didn\'t have nothing to do with the president, but I didn\'t have another set, another company that the outside that we don\'t do anything that","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":909000,"end_time_ms":913000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Well how long did you, um, how long did you have that job?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":913000,"end_time_ms":914000,"num_slots":1,"text":"18 years.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":914000,"end_time_ms":915000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":915000,"end_time_ms":916000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yep.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":916000,"end_time_ms":919000,"num_slots":1,"text":"And when you finished that, what did you go into?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":919000,"end_time_ms":941000,"num_slots":1,"text":"I was, I came back when that was over, we converted back to what we doing now. So I never left the job. That just was a Saturday thing, but I\'ve always been an athlete from Monday through Thursday. That\'s job was feed athletes. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And then you get your days off and then Saturday you do football game. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And that\'s it. Yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":941000,"end_time_ms":944000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Did you get to develop, um, good relationships with the players and the coaches?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":944000,"end_time_ms":959000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh yeah, yeah, yeah. Yeah. You always, yeah, because you\'re going to see these guys every day. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And you\'re gonna see the coaches at some point in time. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So you, you, you try to get to know all the athletes and all the students that many as you can anyway. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":959000,"end_time_ms":965000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Have the athletes changed over time? Are they different now than they were when you first got here? And, and if so, how are they different?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":965000,"end_time_ms":981000,"num_slots":1,"text":"They ain\'t too much different. But see young people get pretty much the same no matter when, when they come in, they all the same kids are gonna be kids, so you just, you expect that out of \'em. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So they, they, they, some of \'em are more mature than others, but you expect that outta kids anyway.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":981000,"end_time_ms":983000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Who\'s your favorite football coach since you\'ve been here?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":983000,"end_time_ms":994000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Favorite football coach have been, I better not say that. <laugh>, I like \'em all that way. I want to, I won\'t eat there. You can\'t do that? No. No. It\'s not, not a thing to do.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":994000,"end_time_ms":1002000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. Well what\'s your favorite game since you\'ve been here? Like if you could pick one Florida football game that was really enjoyable for you? Like mine, I,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1002000,"end_time_ms":1003000,"num_slots":1,"text":"The game last Thursday.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1003000,"end_time_ms":1005000,"num_slots":1,"text":"The game last Thursday? Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Okay.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1005000,"end_time_ms":1016000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Championship game. Any championship game. Okay. That\'s true. So when you get to that point, you know you done did the best, best you can, you got to the high point. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1016000,"end_time_ms":1021000,"num_slots":1,"text":"So you take a lot of um, you know, personal and institutional pride in the achievements of the, of the team and the players. Oh","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1021000,"end_time_ms":1044000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah. Oh yeah, that\'s right. Yeah. We want \'em to do good. Oh, not just football, but all our athletes. So we want all of them to do good because they all work hard and all put in a lot of time. So we don\'t pick just one team. We cater to all, all our athletes because they all hard workers, they all work hard. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So we just don\'t separate one. We will never do that. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So we treat \'em all the same. Mm-hmm <affirmative>.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1044000,"end_time_ms":1054000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Those uh, basketball players that came through for the last couple of years. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. What were your impressions of uh, them? I hear that they hung out all the time together. If you saw one, you usually saw, you know, two or three of \'em together, which was","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1054000,"end_time_ms":1068000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Good. It was a good thing. That way you\'ll know where they at, you know, they\'re not getting in trouble, so, which was a good thing. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Which wasn\'t bad. You want \'em to, to communicate with each other and get along well. Then they produce well. So she worked out. Alright.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1068000,"end_time_ms":1069000,"num_slots":1,"text":"How about Emmett Smith?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1069000,"end_time_ms":1077000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Emmett Smith was great. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And Jordan the whole time he was here. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. I\'m glad he did good with the cowboys and glad he\'s still doing good.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1077000,"end_time_ms":1078000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Kerwin Bell,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1078000,"end_time_ms":1080000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Same. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Yep.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1080000,"end_time_ms":1114000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Anderson. Neil Anderson. Yep. Yep. Shane Matthews, Chris <inaudible>, we go all in August and go away. Way back. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. A lot of them I\'ve seen, they all come to us first. So we see \'em first because we used to be involved in recruiting process when they first get here. So we see the guys from the time they get here. Hopefully it used to be a time you see \'em the whole four years. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. By the time they change, you might see him three. And if you are lucky, you see him four. So you always see those guys from day one until time they leave.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1114000,"end_time_ms":1115000,"num_slots":1,"text":"\'cause they like to eat. So they bring","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1115000,"end_time_ms":1116000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Em. Oh yeah. They know to","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1116000,"end_time_ms":1125000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Eat. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. What kind of things have, have you served them, you know, over a meal? What\'s, what\'s the kind of meal that the athletes would come in a recruiting trip to here? The Gator dining. What do you throw at \'em?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1125000,"end_time_ms":1131000,"num_slots":1,"text":"We throw, put the basics food, steaks, chickens, fish. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. You know, stuff","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1131000,"end_time_ms":1132000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Like that is all you can eat.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1132000,"end_time_ms":1133000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh, you can eat? Oh yeah. They","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1133000,"end_time_ms":1134000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Like","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1134000,"end_time_ms":1147000,"num_slots":1,"text":"That part. Oh yeah. They like that part. <laugh> just don\'t never know what they can eat. But we have a nutrition, uh, uh, dietician on staff. She tell us what to fix and how much, you know, what they should have or whatever. Didn\'t you check somebody afternoon?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1147000,"end_time_ms":1153000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Did they ever get to eat after hours? You, if somebody say, oh, I\'m hungry, can they come in and get something, you know, like in the middle of the night or? No, it\'s kind","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1153000,"end_time_ms":1173000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Of on their own. We close at a certain time. Okay. So they have to be here between the time they supposed to get here. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. In the time they got three hour period to eat from four 30 till nine 30 till eight o\'clock or four to eight. Yeah. So they have any time between that period they can eat, but we don\'t have no special time for \'em.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1173000,"end_time_ms":1179000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Which player over the years ate the most? If you could think of one. He could, he could really put it away.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1179000,"end_time_ms":1184000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh, let\'s see. We had players like Lomo Brown.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1184000,"end_time_ms":1185000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Lmo. Okay. <laugh>","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1185000,"end_time_ms":1191000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Even, believe it or not, doc Lucky. Really? Yep. He used to be one. I was Big eaters. Oh,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1191000,"end_time_ms":1192000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Well Doc\'s still around.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1192000,"end_time_ms":1193000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Doc\'s still around,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1193000,"end_time_ms":1194000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah. The police department. Yeah. So","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1194000,"end_time_ms":1196000,"num_slots":1,"text":"He, he put himself big one. I Big eaters.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1196000,"end_time_ms":1199000,"num_slots":1,"text":"He does a lot of programs with kids in the community and stuff. Kids.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1199000,"end_time_ms":1216000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Right. He\'s a great guy. Uhhuh, <affirmative>. And so pretty much all our big guys eat a lot anyway. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And our swimming team guys, girls, they, they eat a lot, but we, we happy by that. We want \'em to eat and be happy and get, enjoy what they\'re doing. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So we don\'t have no problem with that.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1216000,"end_time_ms":1218000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Uh, do you, do you have children?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1218000,"end_time_ms":1222000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yes, I have. I have one son and four grandsons.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1222000,"end_time_ms":1225000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. What\'s your, what\'s your son\'s name and your grandson\'s names?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1225000,"end_time_ms":1235000,"num_slots":1,"text":"My son\'s name is Gerald Booth. My grandsons is Gerald. I mean John, Bobby, cam and Rob.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1235000,"end_time_ms":1237000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. What about their mom?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1237000,"end_time_ms":1240000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Their mom\'s is in South Carolina.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1240000,"end_time_ms":1244000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. Yeah. Uh, did Gerald go here to the University of Florida?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1244000,"end_time_ms":1247000,"num_slots":1,"text":"No. No. Uh, he local schools in, in the city? Mm-hmm <affirmative>.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1247000,"end_time_ms":1248000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Is he a Gator fan?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1248000,"end_time_ms":1251000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Oh yeah. Definitely. Ain\'t no doubt about that. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Mm-hmm.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1251000,"end_time_ms":1254000,"num_slots":1,"text":"How about the grandkids? You cloth them in orange and blue?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1254000,"end_time_ms":1274000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah, well they pretty much did it on their own. Even my 3-year-old great-grandson is a big Gator fan. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So they, they, they pretty much growed into it because they was already involved because it, they, on Saturday they, they come to the game, uh, look at game every game on TV or whatever. So they was always involved. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So there wasn\'t no problem with that.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1274000,"end_time_ms":1288000,"num_slots":1,"text":"There\'ve been a lot of moments over the course of your history and for the country, for the campus. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Um, what\'s probably something that sticks out in your mind that was really significant that affected the campus since you\'ve been here?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1288000,"end_time_ms":1317000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Let\'s see. Hmm. It\'s a way that the kids get along on campus and the learning facility they have for the kids now. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And the variety of places that the kids have on campus to eat and to interact with each other than they didn\'t have before. Used to be a time when the kids had to eat on campus. They had to go off campus to eat. But we, the company that I worked for provided all these service pretty much on campus for the kids. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. The mos and chilies. And","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1317000,"end_time_ms":1320000,"num_slots":1,"text":"I went to Chili\'s for the first time yesterday and we didn\'t have that when I was here. Yeah. That was","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1320000,"end_time_ms":1321000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Said.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1321000,"end_time_ms":1335000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah. Burger King. Yeah. So now they got these places on campus where the kids can kind of go in and eat and the union offer variety of places and we have Gator Corner and have fresh food and there\'s two all you can eat places.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1335000,"end_time_ms":1347000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Starbucks, they got plenty places. So the kids, it, it\'s a place\'s convenient for the kids. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. And the service that convenient for the kids on campus, which is great now. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Better than it has been in the past. Oh","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1347000,"end_time_ms":1351000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah. Yes sir. I had the buffalo chicken salad yesterday. It was pretty good. Yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1351000,"end_time_ms":1353000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Bad. A little expensive though. Yeah. 8 29, you know.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1353000,"end_time_ms":1355000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah. Well yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1355000,"end_time_ms":1362000,"num_slots":1,"text":"When you talk to Aramark about that They did, I did to cut it back a little bit, you know, cut it back. It was good. It was good. It was big. It was a little much. Well it","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1362000,"end_time_ms":1363000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Was good.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1363000,"end_time_ms":1378000,"num_slots":1,"text":"I\'d like to ask you about some specific events though that happened with, uh, with the campus and, you know, just maybe a reflection or how you felt or anything you want to add. I\'m just gonna mention a couple things. I, I guess the first one would be, uh, the student murders when they happened.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1378000,"end_time_ms":1380000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Nah, I\'d rather not get into that.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1380000,"end_time_ms":1381000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1381000,"end_time_ms":1389000,"num_slots":1,"text":"I, \'cause I don\'t, I don\'t speak of things I don\'t know about or don\'t understand about. So I just rather not get into that.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1389000,"end_time_ms":1404000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. How about the, uh, the, the 1991 win over Florida State? The 14 to nine game here on campus?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1404000,"end_time_ms":1408000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Well, anywhere in old Florida State in any given year, it\'s great. So I, I That\'s fine.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1408000,"end_time_ms":1410000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Why is that? Because","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1410000,"end_time_ms":1431000,"num_slots":1,"text":"We like beating Florida State anyway. It\'s a good rivalry and it\'s a good, anytime you can beat them. They\'re beating us before, but we are beating them more times than they have us. So we, we fine mm-hmm <affirmative>. So we, we just love beating on \'em anyway. \'cause it, they don\'t like Florida, we don\'t like them, so it works out good. It give us something to think about every year at the end of the year. Okay. So it give us something to work towards.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1431000,"end_time_ms":1433000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Who do you look at as the Gator\'s biggest rival?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1433000,"end_time_ms":1435000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Florida State and Georgia.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1435000,"end_time_ms":1437000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. And they, the equal","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1437000,"end_time_ms":1438000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Equals pretty much equal.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1438000,"end_time_ms":1439000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Mm-hmm <affirmative>. Why Georgia?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1439000,"end_time_ms":1448000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Georgia, the fan. Georgia fans always pretty much like Florida State fan. They don\'t like Florida fans. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. So anytime you can beat somebody that don\'t like you, it\'s great. Mm-hmm","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1448000,"end_time_ms":1452000,"num_slots":1,"text":"<affirmative>. Did you go to the game that was here when it rained that one time?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1452000,"end_time_ms":1459000,"num_slots":1,"text":"No, that was smarter than that. I stayed home when it rained. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. I go to the good game when it\'s sunny. Do you, I don\'t mind watching the game. I don\'t like watching in the rain.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1459000,"end_time_ms":1464000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Do you go to Jacksonville and see that game either at the landing or at the stadium?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1464000,"end_time_ms":1467000,"num_slots":1,"text":"I was, I didn\'t go this year, but I went several times. Mm-hmm <affirmative>.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1467000,"end_time_ms":1470000,"num_slots":1,"text":"What do you think about the atmosphere of that game over in Jacksonville?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1470000,"end_time_ms":1482000,"num_slots":1,"text":"It\'s not bad. You just got to watch what you\'re doing and watch where you\'re going. Mm-hmm <affirmative>. That\'s all Jackson. There\'s no worse than the other city. You just got to be be in the right place at the right time. You just watch what you\'re doing. That\'s all. Mm-hmm","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1482000,"end_time_ms":1491000,"num_slots":1,"text":"<affirmative>. So Florida State, Georgia. What about Auburn? You know, we don\'t play them every year anymore, but that used to be a big rival. Yeah,","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1491000,"end_time_ms":1492000,"num_slots":1,"text":"It\'s okay.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1492000,"end_time_ms":1508000,"num_slots":1,"text":"In fact, when you said your favorite game was last Thursday, I was thinking my favorite game was when, here when Kerwin lipped into the end zone and scored that touchdown and then we got the two point conversion and came back. You know, we were down in the fourth quarter and came back and beat Auburn here when Colonel was, uh, quarterback. Quarterback. Yeah.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1508000,"end_time_ms":1529000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Probably pretty much. But anytime you get all in Tennessee, Georgia, uh, for the state, all of those better rivals. Them teams. Good team you want to beat anyway. So anytime you can beat any one of those, it\'s fine. Even we do not overlooking all of \'em, but Auburn\'s not as big as the Tennessee game in the Georgia and Florida state game. Yeah. To me, that\'s just my opinion.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1529000,"end_time_ms":1537000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Yeah. I, I agree. To me, it\'s Georgia, you\'re right. Florida State is kind of like, well, you know, it\'s good to beat them, but Right. Georgia\'s the one that matters. It\'s just a bad year when we lose Georgia.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1537000,"end_time_ms":1543000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Georgia. Oh yeah. Yeah. Okay. Well my time up. I gotta get outta here. But anyway, what else you got quick for another?","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S1","tier":"Speaker 0","start_time_ms":1543000,"end_time_ms":1575000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Well, I\'ll tell you what, it\'s always good to end the interview. Right. Allowing the person that I\'ve spoken to first I want thank you right. So much for this opportunity and letting Mark in with us as well. Okay. And, um, just if you have any kind of reflection that, that you\'d like to offer, I\'d like to end the interview on your words. So I\'m gonna just say thank you for allowing it. Right. And then when you get done saying whatever it might be, your reflection on the interview, on your time right here at the University of Florida on the future, uh, you know, I mean we didn\'t talk about Barack Obama, you know, whatever. Right. Anything, anything that you\'d like to offer that\'ll, that\'ll close the interview.","dependents":[]},{"speaker":"S2","tier":"Speaker 1","start_time_ms":1575000,"end_time_ms":1578000,"num_slots":1,"text":"Okay. Well I\'d just like to thank for you taking your time out to grant me this interview and try to find out what the history of the University of Florida. And again, I\'m glad to know that we finally got ourself a black president as of next Tuesday. And I\'m glad things change and you know, and hopefully everything continue to be the same in the future, only for the bedside. We\'re looking for the better part. And so if, if the University of Florida keeps function at the way they are and things keep turning, we\'ll be fine. And it been, it\'s always a privilege to work with a company like Aramark that provide services for the students on campus, which is great. We enjoy that and it\'s not bad. And they really willing to be flexible with the kids. When the kids want something, they try to provide it for them. So it\'s not a bad idea. And I\'ve seen a lot of changes on this campus and it\'s ones, I\'ve seen it for the best and I just hope it continue to go in the way that it\'s going. And if you do that, we\'ll be fine. And again, I thank you both for the opportunity to tell a little bit of history of University of Florida for me, John Booth, which is fine. Thanks a lot. Thank you Mr. Booth. All right. Appreciate it. Y\'all take care.","dependents":[]}]}')}}]);
